Beyond the described approaches that construct and leverage embeddings for link prediction, LLMs may also be directly used in a prompting setting to find suitable links between entities, with existing methods described in detail in the following Section (ref). 
As with the previous approaches that purely use LLMs, prompt-based approaches are directly applicable for ILP and are commonly evaluated in this setting [bosselut-etal-2019-comet,jiang2020can,petroniLAMA2019,shinAutoPrompt2020,zhong2021factual].